{
    "tha-ap398:0.1_0": "The senior monks, Householders,",
    "tha-ap398:0.2_0": "With Pilindavaccha",
    "tha-ap398:0.3_0": "Remember the senior monks",
    "tha-ap398:1.1_0": "I plunged into the lake,",
    "tha-ap398:1.2_0": "Virūpakkha,",
    "tha-ap398:1.3_0": "I’ve been a good speaker,",
    "tha-ap398:1.4_0": "even by your own mother.",
    "tha-ap398:10.1_0": "quickly enter the hermitage,",
    "tha-ap398:10.2_0": "to stay in the presence of me.",
    "tha-ap398:10.3_0": "if he wants to take medicine;",
    "tha-ap398:10.4_0": "I summoned him.",
    "tha-ap398:11.1_0": "When I’ve practiced this,",
    "tha-ap398:11.2_0": "than respectful, lacking respect for others.",
    "tha-ap398:11.3_0": "They gathered together,",
    "tha-ap398:11.4_0": "Respect for the Teacher.",
    "tha-ap398:12.1_0": "quickly throw them down",
    "tha-ap398:12.2_0": "all around,",
    "tha-ap398:12.3_0": "Having prepared a cool water,",
    "tha-ap398:12.4_0": "before the best of Buddhas.",
    "tha-ap398:13.1_0": "until the great hero,",
    "tha-ap398:13.2_0": "of universal understanding and superior knowledge,",
    "tha-ap398:13.3_0": "quickly extinguish it,",
    "tha-ap398:13.4_0": "he is the great hermit,",
    "tha-ap398:14.1_0": "Seeing the tranquility,",
    "tha-ap398:14.2_0": "a great producer of folk.",
    "tha-ap398:14.3_0": "sits down on the seat",
    "tha-ap398:14.4_0": "these verses.",
    "tha-ap398:15.1_0": "‘Here’s me out the tonics,",
    "tha-ap398:15.2_0": "and even those who are sick,",
    "tha-ap398:15.3_0": "I’ll expel them",
    "tha-ap398:15.4_0": "listen to me.",
    "tha-ap398:16.1_0": "Twenty thousands",
    "tha-ap398:16.2_0": "heavenly delight,",
    "tha-ap398:16.3_0": "if, when there are waters,",
    "tha-ap398:16.4_0": "rejoice.",
    "tha-ap398:17.1_0": "I plunged into the human realm,",
    "tha-ap398:17.2_0": "with bright words,",
    "tha-ap398:17.3_0": "King Kikī,",
    "tha-ap398:17.4_0": "thinking, “There will be a wheel-turning monarch.”",
    "tha-ap398:18.1_0": "Projecting wisdom is the five-five years,",
    "tha-ap398:18.2_0": "An aristocrat is untouched.",
    "tha-ap398:18.3_0": "looks all around the four directions,",
    "tha-ap398:18.4_0": "I was lord of India.",
    "tha-ap398:19.1_0": "Endowed with the seven gems,",
    "tha-ap398:19.2_0": "Mahāpajāpatī Gotamī,",
    "tha-ap398:19.3_0": "Looking back the Thirty-Three,",
    "tha-ap398:19.4_0": "having hermits made the hermitage.",
    "tha-ap398:2.1_0": "for many cities",
    "tha-ap398:2.2_0": "flowering on a riverbank,",
    "tha-ap398:2.3_0": "For there are many more than",
    "tha-ap398:2.4_0": "who live as tenders.",
    "tha-ap398:20.1_0": "you’re like a human being,",
    "tha-ap398:20.2_0": "thinking, “I’ll be healthy.”",
    "tha-ap398:20.3_0": "They’ve escaped the senses,",
    "tha-ap398:20.4_0": "will fall sick.",
    "tha-ap398:21.1_0": "Through countless eons",
    "tha-ap398:21.2_0": "a family born in this life,",
    "tha-ap398:21.3_0": "Gotama, his clan,",
    "tha-ap398:21.4_0": "The Teacher will be in the world.",
    "tha-ap398:22.1_0": "that Kassapa is the supreme person,",
    "tha-ap398:22.2_0": "I left the teaching.",
    "tha-ap398:22.3_0": "complete understanding",
    "tha-ap398:22.4_0": "will realize quenching.",
    "tha-ap398:23.1_0": "having conquered the corruptions,",
    "tha-ap398:23.2_0": "Sladly, it will fall.",
    "tha-ap398:23.3_0": "Pakudha Kaccāyana,",
    "tha-ap398:23.4_0": "for his disciple who is the Teacher.",
    "tha-ap398:24.1_0": "Directly knowing this:",
    "tha-ap398:24.2_0": "Gotama is a breakable,",
    "tha-ap398:24.3_0": "But the Saṅgha of monks,",
    "tha-ap398:24.4_0": "will stand aside.’",
    "tha-ap398:25.1_0": "The Buddha, imagined,",
    "tha-ap398:25.2_0": "from the world to the next,",
    "tha-ap398:25.3_0": "Remembering the meditators of seclusion,",
    "tha-ap398:25.4_0": "That’s why I’m safe.",
    "tha-ap398:26.1_0": "That great hero has gone forth",
    "tha-ap398:26.2_0": "of all the world’s compassion,",
    "tha-ap398:26.3_0": "and because of all that, Tapussa,",
    "tha-ap398:26.4_0": "confidence in the teaching.",
    "tha-ap398:27.1_0": "I have done good deeds",
    "tha-ap398:27.2_0": "in a fertile field,",
    "tha-ap398:27.3_0": "But I’m not able to reply,",
    "tha-ap398:27.4_0": "then, spurning what was well done.",
    "tha-ap398:28.1_0": "‘I’m fortunate, so very fortunate,",
    "tha-ap398:28.2_0": "I’m horrifyingable,",
    "tha-ap398:28.3_0": "he does just that.",
    "tha-ap398:28.4_0": "I’ve attained the state of grace.",
    "tha-ap398:29.1_0": "are all completely understood:",
    "tha-ap398:29.2_0": "Gotama is a breakable,",
    "tha-ap398:29.3_0": "But the Saṅgha of monks,",
    "tha-ap398:29.4_0": "I left behind me.",
    "tha-ap398:3.1_0": "Though there are many different kinds of stains,",
    "tha-ap398:3.2_0": "and jujube seeds.",
    "tha-ap398:3.3_0": "It was clasping to grass,",
    "tha-ap398:3.4_0": "and a flower’s flowers.",
    "tha-ap398:30.1_0": "These young maidens",
    "tha-ap398:30.2_0": "from where deeds I want.",
    "tha-ap398:30.3_0": "I’m not aware of any bad places",
    "tha-ap398:30.4_0": "This is the fruit for tonics.",
    "tha-ap398:31.1_0": "My defilements have been burnt away by practicing absorption—",
    "tha-ap398:31.2_0": "rebirth into all states of existence is eradicated,",
    "tha-ap398:31.3_0": "with all defilements ended,",
    "tha-ap398:31.4_0": "Now there is no further existence.",
    "tha-ap398:32.1_0": "It was truly for me",
    "tha-ap398:32.2_0": "... “I attained the noble ones,” ...",
    "tha-ap398:32.3_0": "and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions.”",
    "tha-ap398:33.1_0": "Attaining the four kinds of textual analysis",
    "tha-ap398:33.2_0": "... “I attained the noble ones,” ...",
    "tha-ap398:33.3_0": "and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions.”",
    "tha-ap398:34.1_0": "That is how these verses were recited by the senior venerable Bakkula.",
    "tha-ap398:35.1_0": "The sixth subduing of the senior monks.",
    "tha-ap398:4.1_0": "The Belaṭṭhasīsa,",
    "tha-ap398:4.2_0": "so long as the fingers,",
    "tha-ap398:4.3_0": "for many people are Mahānāma,",
    "tha-ap398:4.4_0": "and the loved ones.",
    "tha-ap398:5.1_0": "Kosambī,",
    "tha-ap398:5.2_0": "and settlement in broads.",
    "tha-ap398:5.3_0": "My breast is like a packnowledge,",
    "tha-ap398:5.4_0": "that you stay under your control.",
    "tha-ap398:6.1_0": "The Buddha, imagined,",
    "tha-ap398:6.2_0": "from the world to the next,",
    "tha-ap398:6.3_0": "Rejecting the retreat,",
    "tha-ap398:6.4_0": "That’s why I’m safe.",
    "tha-ap398:7.1_0": "People who have found peace the great hero,",
    "tha-ap398:7.2_0": "I’m beyond a lady’s army.",
    "tha-ap398:7.3_0": "sticks the world with its gods,",
    "tha-ap398:7.4_0": "by winds that are opened.",
    "tha-ap398:8.1_0": "I wandered in the wilderness,",
    "tha-ap398:8.2_0": "I saw the world speedy person",
    "tha-ap398:8.3_0": "Guttā, the Awakened One",
    "tha-ap398:8.4_0": "so even and fraud.",
    "tha-ap398:9.1_0": "Though he sees",
    "tha-ap398:9.2_0": "I flew off them with a stick.",
    "tha-ap398:9.3_0": "For the life of the Buddha,",
    "tha-ap398:9.4_0": "They’re sick."
}